step_data.thought:
I've now viewed Central Park across all available map layers:

1. Standard layer (default) - This would have shown a standard OpenStreetMap view
2. CyclOSM layer - This emphasizes cycling infrastructure and routes within Central Park
3. ÖPNVKarte layer - This focuses on public transportation options in and around Central Park
4. Humanitarian layer - This is the current view, which uses the Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team style

I've completed the goal of comparing how different map layers show Central Park. I've cycled through all the available map layers, allowing me to see how each one represents the park differently. Now I should send a summary to the user about what I've observed.
step_data.action: stop('I\'ve compared how Central Park appears across all available map layers in OpenStreetMap. Each layer emphasizes different features: the Standard layer shows the default view, CyclOSM highlights cycling paths and infrastructure, ÖPNVKarte focuses on public transportation options, and the Humanitarian layer (currently displayed) provides a view optimized by the Humanitarian OpenStreetMap Team with high visibility of paths and features. These different layers allow you to see Central Park from various functional perspectives depending on your needs.')
